name: Colorado Department of Public Health and Environment
street: 4300 Cherry Creek Dr S, Bldg A
directions: Left past the guard's desk on the right side of the hallway. Before the "regular" bathrooms.
comment: These are for employees and citizens conducting business with the Department only.

name: Jeanine Jensen
directions: Trader Joe's - single floor, usually in the rear of the store.
comment: No need to be a paying customer.  I confirmed with the store manager in Oakland (Rockridge store) that these gender neutral, accessible, changing table restrooms are Trader Joe's Company policy.

name: UNE Dental School
directions: Walking into the dental clinic, there are two restrooms to the right that are single stall unisex restrooms.
comment: You have to be a patient at the dental clinic - which I recommend! Cheaper dental work, and you’re helping save the world by being their guinea pig

name: San Gabriel Unitarian Universalist Fellowship
directions: Both restrooms in the main building and each restroom in the other two buildings are single occupancy.
comment: This congregation took a special course in order to be more inclusive and be a safe, welcoming space to all. They are quite vocal about social justice and human rights. This is a safe place, and they look to help.

name: Abertay University
directions: Second Floor of the Kydd Building, above reception.

name: Nip and Growler Craft Ale House
directions: At the back of the alehouse, to the left of the bar is the corridor for the toilets.
comment: They would most likely prefer you to be a paying customer but are an LGBTQIA+ friendly bar and owned by individuals who are part of it themselves. If you are in need and do not feel safe elsewhere they will most likely be fine, maybe a small donation of some pennies to the local pride charity pot?

name: Starbucks
directions: To the right of the entrance, by the counter/merchandise
comment: Open to the public, no purchase required

name: Casey's General Store
directions: Around the backside of the counter.
comment: The corporate office confirmed they are safe. They are in process of converting all bathrooms to gender neutral. Corporate says if any employee has issue with an individual using restroom to immediately call corporate office with employee's name.
